	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Charleston</placeName> <date>Decr. 26&#47;47</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd I Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">My dear Sir&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">Some time<lb/> has elapsed since I have had<lb/> a line from you&#44;  I trust however<add>&#63;</add><lb/> your silence has not been produ<lb/>&#61;ced by indisposition &#38; that <sic>you</sic> health<lb/> has much improved.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Pray how did <persName>Mr Woolf</persName> manage<lb/> I noticed his passing through our city<lb/> but did not see him</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I reced. the last no of the Publication<lb/> Society&#44; &#38; they have been distributed<lb/> you continue to send more nos.<lb/> to the orthodox Sunday School than<lb/> they have subscribed for.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I recd no Occident for <date>Nov</date> or<lb/> <date>decr.</date> for <persName>Miss Simpson</persName>&#44; how does this<lb/> happen.  Nor was there one recd for<lb/> <date>July</date>&#44; please send them as she com<lb/>&#61;plains &#38; perhaps would not pay her<lb/> subscription&#44; for I tell them we do<lb/> not underwrite the mail.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Miss Seixas</persName> was married last <date>Wednes<lb/>day</date> evening at 7 oclock Ours is a pro</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>gressive age.  We <add>&#63;</add>fully married<lb/> in the early part of the day&#44; &#38;<lb/> we refine <del> <add>&#63;</add> </del> upon &#38; <sic>mary</sic> as near<lb/> the time for going to bed as decency<lb/> would allow.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">We are to have another wed<lb/>&#61;ding soon <persName>Miss Tobias</persName> to <persName>Mr<lb/> Minas<add>&#63;</add></persName> <add>&#63;</add> I am apprehensive<lb/> there will be some difficulty about<lb/> who is to marry them&#44; for report says<lb/> that he is one who has never been<lb/> circumcised.  Do you know any<lb/> thing of it &#38; does it not prevent a man<lb/> from being married by a Jewish congregation<lb/>  Is a man a <sic>jew</sic> altho his father &#38; mother<lb/> are Jews&#44; when he is uncircumcised&#63;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Miss <add>&#63;</add></persName> &#38; <persName>Miss Peixatto</persName> are spending<lb/> the winter with us&#8212;I <del>thought</del> you<lb/> were going to visit us this winter</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">News scarce.  Hoping this will meet<lb/> you well in which <add>hope</add> I am joined<lb/> by mother sisters &#38; newphews&#8212;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Your friend</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">Samuel Hart Sen.</persName></p>
		</body>
